Fortis Bank to be nationalised by Benelux governments
The Benelux countries are helping with partial nationalisation because of the spillover effect of the US credit crisis – the first European – at the Belgian-Dutch bank, Fortison: the three countries are supporting the financial and insurance institution with Hungarian interests with a total of EUR 11.2 billion.
The Belgian, Luxembourg and Dutch governments agreed at the highest level at the end of the week, involving the President of the European Central Bank and the European Commission’s competition authority.
In the euro area, Fortis Bank is the first major crisis in the wake of an international financial market crisis that has been ringing in waves for more than a year, and the decisions made in the case of the bank can therefore be regarded as precedent-setting in some respects.
According to the decision taken on Sunday night, all three states acquire nearly half (49%) of the bank’s existing assets.
